The Federal National MortgageAssociation said it will begin purchasing 10 and 20-year fixedrate mortgages in addition to 15 and 30 year mortgages.    It said the new intermediate term mortgage purchaseprograms are designed to offer home buyers more home financingflexibility.    Edward J. Pinto, FNMA's Senior Vice President, saidintermediate term mortgages offer "lower interest rates,substantial interest savings, lower inflation rates and, inmany cases, faster equity build-up" than longer-term mortgages. Reuter&#3;